text: Pararistolochia ceropegioides is a plant species of family Aristolochiaceae. It is found in Cameroon and Gabon. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests and subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== * ceropegioides Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
